# QR System Data Models

## Payment Template Structure

Templates store only payment data, never pre-generated QR codes:

```typescript
interface PaymentTemplate {
  id: UUID;
  userId: UUID;
  name: string;           // "Haircut", "Consultation", etc.
  amount: number;         // EUR amount
  description: string;    // Payment description
  iban: string;          // User's Slovak IBAN
  color: string;         // UI theming (#blue, #green)
  icon: string;          // UI icon (scissors, stethoscope)
  usageCount: number;    // Analytics tracking
  createdAt: Date;
  isActive: boolean;
}
```

## Generated Transaction Structure

Each QR generation creates a transaction record for analytics:

```typescript
interface GeneratedTransaction {
  id: UUID;
  templateId: UUID;
  templateName: string;    // Preserved if template deleted
  amount: number;
  variableSymbol: string;  // Unique 8-digit identifier
  qrData: string;         // Generated BySquare QR string
  generatedAt: Date;
  status: 'generated' | 'shown' | 'paid';
}
```

## Variable Symbol Generation

Unique 8-digit identifier for each transaction:

```typescript
function generateVariableSymbol(): string {
  const timestamp = Date.now().toString().slice(-6); // Last 6 digits
  const random = Math.floor(Math.random() * 100).toString().padStart(2, '0');
  return timestamp + random; // e.g., "84523401"
}
```

These models ensure unique tracking, complete analytics, and proper accounting integration.
